{{Infobox airport | name = Bangassou Airport | IATA = BGU | ICAO = FEFG | type = Public | city-served = [[Bangassou]], [[Central African Republic]] | location = | elevation-f = 1640 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|4|47|08|N|22|47|00|E|region:CF_type:airport|name=Bangassou Airport (Bangassou)|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Central African Republic | pushpin_label = '''BGU''' | pushpin_map_caption = Location of Bangassou Airport in the Central African Republic | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 09/27 | r1-length-f = | r1-length-m = 1805 | r1-surface = Grass | footnotes = Source: Landings.com<ref name="Landings">[http://aerobaticsweb.org/cgi-bin/search_apt?FEFG Airport record for Bangassou Airport] at Landings.com. Retrieved 2013-08-25</ref> Google Maps<ref name="Google">{{Google maps|url=https://maps.google.com/maps?ht=en&z=13&t=k&q=4.78569444444444,22.7826388888889+%28Bangassou+Airport%29|title=location of Bangassou Airport|accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref> GCM<ref>{{GCM|BGU|Bangassou Airport}}</ref> }}
'''Bangassou Airport''' {{Airport codes|BGU|FEFG}} is an airport serving [[Bangassou]], a city on the [[Mbomou River]] in the [[Mbomou]] prefecture of the [[Central African Republic]]. The Mbomou River forms the local border with the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
The airport is {{convert|5|km}} northwest of the city, near the Mbari River, a tributary of the Mbomou.
