The '''Banu Sa'd''' ({{lang-ar|بنو سعد}} / [[ALA-LC]]: ''Banū Saʾd'') was one of the [[tribes of Arabia during Muhammad's era]]. The Banu Sa'd were a subgroup of the larger [[Hawazin]] tribal confederation. They were notable for being allies to the [[polytheist]] [[Mecca]]ns and warring with the [[Muslims]] during Islam's early days.{{cn|date=May 2015}} [[Halima Sadia]], Muhammad's [[wet nurse]], belonged to this tribe.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Nicolle|first1=David|title=The great Islamic conquests AD 632-750|date=2009|publisher=Osprey|location=Oxford|isbn=1846032733|page=19|edition=1. publ.}}</ref>

