The '''Embassy of Russia in Tbilisi''' was the [[diplomatic mission]] of the [[Russian Federation]] to the [[Georgia (country)|Republic of Georgia]]. The [[Chancery (building)|chancery]] is located at 51 Chavchavadze Avenue in [[Tbilisi]].<ref>{{cite web
  | script-title=ru:Грузия
  | publisher = [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Russia)]]
  | url = http://www.mid.ru/zu_r.nsf/e0f3cd1a55ff248dc32571e7003f460b/16411e7f4d1b7ca1432569bd00234ec3?OpenDocument
  | accessdate = 2008-08-13 |language=ru}}</ref> On August 29, 2008, Georgia ordered the Russian ambassador [[Vyacheslav Kovalenko]] and all other Russian diplomats to leave the country and close the embassy and severed diplomatic relations with Russia.<ref>[http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5g8JIulsM3ioTtotqyf621zaYjwwg Georgia breaks relations with Russia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081107093623/http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5g8JIulsM3ioTtotqyf621zaYjwwg |date=2008-11-07 }}</ref> Russia and Georgia had previously fought a five-day [[2008 South Ossetia war|war]] over two Georgian breakaway regions ([[Abkhazia]] and [[South Ossetia]]) declaring independence. The Russian Federation is represented through the Russian Federation Interests Section of the Embassy of Switzerland in Georgia.

