nnel who will operate the two French-built {{sclass2-|Scorpène|submarine|2}}s planned for the Royal Malaysian Navy. Despite official statements in 2009 that ''Ouessant'' had been sold to Malaysia,<ref>{{cite web | title = Ministry of Foreign Affairs | url = http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fr/article_imprim.php3?id_article=79184 }}</ref> the position remained unclear.<ref>{{cite web | title = So Who Owns The Ouessant Actually? | url = http://securemalaysia.blogspot.com/2009/01/so-who-owns-ouessant-actually.html }}</ref> Because of ''Ouessant''{{'}}s role in the establishment of the Malaysian submarine forces, plans to return the vessel to Malaysia to serve as a [[museum ship]] were announced in July 2009.;<ref>{{cite web | title = Ouessant To Be A Museum In Malaysia? | url = http://securemalaysia.blogspot.com/2009/07/ouessant-to-be-museum-in-malaysia.html}}</ref> ''Ouessant'' was formally transferred to the Malaysian Government on 23 September 2011<ref>{{cite web | title = Transfer of submarine ''Ouessant'' | url = http://www.kln.gov.my/web/fra_paris/home/-/asset_publisher/8pPT/blog/signing-ceremony-for-the-transfer-of-ownership-of-the-agosta-70-type-submarine-to-the-malaysian-government-paris-23-september-2011?redirect=%2Fweb%2Ffra_paris%2Fhome }}</ref> to be transported to [[Klebang]], Malacca to become a museum.
