{{short description|A group of geologic formations in the subsurface of the Netherlands and adjacent parts of the North Sea.}} {| class="toccolours" style="float:right; margin-left: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; font-size: 85%;" |colspan="2"|'''[[Formation (stratigraphy)|Formations]], [[Member (stratigraphy)|members]] and [[stratum|layers]] after [[TNO-NITG|NITG-TNO]]''' |- | bgcolor="Lightgrey" colspan="3" | [[marine (ocean)|marine]] |- | rowspan="4" bgcolor="Powderblue" |[[Dongen Formation]] DO | bgcolor="Powderblue" |[[Asse Member]] DOAS |- | bgcolor="Powderblue" |[[Brussel Member]] DOBR |- | bgcolor="Powderblue" |[[Ieper Member]] DOIE |- | bgcolor="Powderblue" |[[Oosteind Member]] DOOO | bgcolor="Powderblue" |[[Basal Dongen Tuffite]] DOOOBT |- | rowspan="5" bgcolor="Lightsteelblue" |[[Landen Formation]] LA | bgcolor="Lightsteelblue" |[[Gelinden Member]] LAGE |- | bgcolor="Lightsteelblue" |[[Liessel Member]] LALI |- | bgcolor="Lightsteelblue" |[[Orp Member]] LAOR |- | bgcolor="Lightsteelblue" |[[Reusel Member]] LARE |- | bgcolor="Lightsteelblue" |[[Swalmen Member]] LASW |} The '''Lower North Sea Group''' (abbreviation: NL) is a [[group (stratigraphy)|group]] of [[formation (stratigraphy)|geologic formations]] in the [[Subsurface (geology)|subsurface]] of the [[Netherlands]] and adjacent parts of the [[North Sea]].
The group is part of the [[North Sea Supergroup]] and consists of two marine formations of early [[Paleogene]] age, the older [[Landen Formation]] and younger [[Dongen Formation]]. It is in most places stratigraphically on top of the [[Late Cretaceous]] [[Chalk Group]] and overlain by the late Paleogene [[Middle North Sea Group]].
The Lower North Sea Group [[outcrop|crops out]] in a few spots in the south of the Netherlands but is mostly overlain by younger deposits. It can be found in the subsurface of most of the Netherlands.
