'''Olav Orheim''' (born 22 February 1942) is a Norwegian [[glaciology|glaciologist]]. He served as director of the [[Norwegian Polar Institute]] from 1993 to 2005. He was appointed associate professor in glaciology at the [[University of Bergen]] in 1989. Orheim was a central participant in the establishment of the research station [[Troll (research station)|Troll]] in [[Queen Maud Land]] in [[Antarctica]].<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Olav Orheim |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=[[Kunnskapsforlaget]] |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Olav_Orheim |language=Norwegian | accessdate=27 August 2011 }}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Olav Orheim |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Nils |last=Paulsen |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Olav_Orheim/utdypning |language=Norwegian|accessdate=27 August 2011}}</ref>
