'''Assado''' is a roasted fish dish in [[Portugal]] served with a Portuguese sausage (''{{lang|pt|[[linguiça]]}}'' or ''{{lang|pt|[[chorizo|chouriço]]}}''), chopped [[bacon]] or ''{{lang|pt|[[presunto]]}}'', and chopped onions. The two most common fish used are [[salmon]] and [[cod]].

