'''Áfengis- og tóbaksverslun ríkisins''' or '''ÁTVR''' (''State Alcohol and Tobacco Company of Iceland'' in [[English language|English]]) is a [[public ownership|state owned]] company that has a monopoly on the sale of [[alcoholic beverage]]s and tobacco in [[Iceland]]. It runs the [[Vínbúð]] chain, often called ''Ríkið'' (The State) after its owner.<ref>[http://timarit.is/view_page_init.jsp?pageId=3059958 Dómsmálaráðherra setur áfengisbann;grein í DV 1976]</ref><ref>[http://timarit.is/view_page_init.jsp?pageId=1471622 Áfenginu lokað vegna ástandsins; grein í Morgunblaðinu 1976]</ref>

